Three U.S. Senators said they willpropose a temporary ban on imports of all Toshiba products dueto the company's illegal sales of sensitive high-technologygoods to the Soviet Union.    Senator Jake Garn, John Heinz and Richard Selby said at ahearing of the senate banking committee on export control, theywill offer the proposal as part of a major trade bill when itis brought before the senate this summer.    Garn, a Utah Republican, said "I am talking about specificretribution on a company that endangers the security of theirown country and ours." Reuter&#3;